# Preferences -- EXAMPLE / TEMPLATE

Copy this file to your Tempo content dir as `preferences.md` (default
`<content_root>/preferences.md`, redirect with `TEMPO_CONTENT_DIR`) and edit
it. UNLIKE the other trackers (food.md, weight.md, races.md, etc.) which are
append-only logs, this file is an **edit-in-place profile**: hand-edit the
typed sections when your numbers change, hand-edit the prose sections any
time you'd like the coach to see something. The file is never committed (the
content dir lives outside the repo tree). The numbers below are synthetic
textbook placeholders -- replace with yours.

The four typed sections (`Physiology`, `Units`, `Nutrition`) are parsed as
structured config; every other H2 section is captured verbatim as a prose
section the coach can read via `Read training/preferences.md`.

See `docs/PREFERENCES.md` for the full grammar + lenient-parsing contract.

## Physiology

threshold_pace: 4:00/km          # accepted forms: M:SS/mi, M:SS/km, NNN s/km, NNN
max_hr: 190                      # measured or estimated; feeds load.py hr-TSS
resting_hr: 50                   # 7d morning average from the watch
threshold_hr: 175                # optional; if absent load.py uses ~0.92*max_hr

## Units

distance: km                     # km | miles (also accepted: mi, mile, kilometres)
pace: min_per_km                 # min_per_km | min_per_mile (also: min/km, mpk, min/mi, mpm)

## Nutrition

target_kcal: 2200                # optional; enables 7d delta in nutrition + recovery reports

## Training week

Monday: easy doubles, ~12 km
Tuesday: threshold day (sometimes double threshold, sometimes threshold + easy)
Wednesday: medium-long, 14-16 km steady
Thursday: single easy
Friday: marathon-pace work OR easy (inverse of Sunday)
Saturday: easy
Sunday: long with marathon-pace work OR pure easy (inverse of Friday)
Note: don't typically do MP work on both Fri AND Sun in the same week.

## Goals / current focus

- Build aerobic base through the spring
- A-race: autumn marathon, sub-3 hour goal
- Avoid the recurring left-Achilles niggle by capping any single week below 100 km

# What gets parsed vs. read

The lenient parser ONLY extracts typed fields from the three named sections
above (`Physiology`, `Units`, `Nutrition`). Unknown keys inside a typed
section are silently ignored (forward-compat). Any other `## Header` is
captured verbatim into the parsed context's `prose_sections` dict, keyed by
the lowercased + stripped header text -- the coach reads it when relevant,
the analysis layer never interprets it. Free-form prose between sections,
the leading `# Preferences` H1, and any preamble before the first H2 are all
discarded by the parser (but visible when the coach reads the file).

# What NOT to do

Malformed typed-section values stay at their default and the line number
lands in `PreferencesContext.malformed_lines`. Examples (shown with a
leading `~` so the parser doesn't see them as live values):

  * `~ threshold_pace: 4 min/mi`     -- missing seconds component (needs M:SS/unit).
  * `~ max_hr: high`                 -- not parseable as int.
  * `~ target_kcal: about 2200`      -- prose where a number is required.

_Tempo's parser is lenient: missing file degrades to `present=False`,
malformed values leave the field at its default (line number captured in
`PreferencesContext.malformed_lines`), unknown keys / unrecognised sections
do not raise. See `docs/PREFERENCES.md` for the full contract._
